<lb/>109/A.
<opener><address><addrLine>Headquarters Irish Command,</addrLine>
<addrLine>Parkgate, Dublin.</addrLine></address>
<dateline><date>20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> May, 1916.</date></dateline>
<salute>Madam,</salute></opener>
<p>In reply to your letter of the 17th instant, I
<lb/> have to inform you that the Court Martial on Mr Desmond
<lb/> Fitzgerald was <del>considered</del><add>confirmed</add> to-day by the General Officer
<lb/> Commanding in Chief. He was sentenced by the Court to
<lb/> twenty years Penal Servitude ten years of which were
<lb/> remitted by the General Officer Commanding in Chief. He
<lb/> will be removed to Mountjoy Prison where he will be permitted
<lb/> the visit usually allowed to convicts during the
<lb/> first week of their sentences. Application should therefore
<lb/> be made to the Governor, Mountjoy Prison. Any
<lb/> property belonging to Mr.Fitzgerald which may be found in
<lb/> Richmond Barracks will be forwarded to you.</p>
<closer><salute>Yours faithfully,</salute>
<signed>J.H.G.Stantin</signed>
<lb/><add>for</add> Brig.Genl.
<lb/>D.A.G.
<address><addrLine>Mrs Fitzgerald,</addrLine>
<addrLine>2 Loretta Villas,</addrLine>
<addrLine>BRAY</addrLine></address></closer>.
        
    

    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        

         

